The paper deals with the computational complexity of solving puzzles in Bloxorz, which involves tilting a block on a grid to reach a destination square. This falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) as the authors analyze the complexity of solving the puzzle. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) to solve the puzzle. Additionally, the authors examine the hardness of the puzzle, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper involves the manipulation of geometric objects on a grid, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG).
